le> Shifting Sight</span><hr size=1> Since I get alot of tells on how I see far far far off into the distance of a zone without moving, here is the trick.  Wizards and some other casters (think necro or chanter) have a spell called Shifting Sight.  Level 39 for a wizard.  I can't remember if there's a lower level one, I could be thinking wrong though.  Anyways, it allows me to see out of whatever NPC or PC's perspective without agro.  Then I can F9 out and see around them.  Then, after that, I can target yet another PC or NPC near them and cast shifting sight again to change perspective.  I can basically go clear across a zone without moving my character.  It's great if there's no tracker around, but the down fall is that it's much slower to get around with it rather than track.  It can also be a great help if you cast it on a puller, then you can basically tell them exactly where to go if there's a special mob to grab or let them know if danger is around the corner.  Dang...being a wizard isn't so bad I guess =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=2.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=2.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm4.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/them